import textwrap
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def mse_score_plot(df, y_min = None,  y_max = None):  
    #df['MODEL'] = df['MODEL'].apply(lambda x: '\n'.join(textwrap.wrap(x, 20)))
    # A Seaborn catplot hasznlata, amely lehetv teszi az adatok "facet"-szer brzolst.
    ax = sns.barplot(x='MODEL', y='MSE', data=df, palette='Blues_d',)
    if y_min is not None or y_max is not None:
        y_max = y_max*1.2
        ax.set_ylim(ymin=y_min, ymax=y_max)
    plt.xticks(rotation=50)
    plt.xlabel('')  
    plt.ylabel('MSE')
    plt.title('MSE of Different Models')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def r2_score_plot(df, y_min = None,  y_max = None):  
    ax = sns.barplot(x='MODEL', y='R2', data=df, palette='Blues_d',)
    if y_min is not None or y_max is not None:
        y_max = y_max*1.2
        ax.set_ylim(ymin=y_min, ymax=y_max)
    plt.xticks(rotation=50)
    plt.xlabel('')  
    plt.ylabel('R2')
    plt.title('R2 of Different Models')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()

def df_grouping(df_cv,col_from, col_to):
    """
    Create a grouped DataFrame by selecting a specific range of columns from an existing DataFrame.

    Parameters:
    df_cv (pandas.DataFrame): The input DataFrame from which to select columns.
    col_from (int): The starting index of the column range to be included in the new DataFrame.
    col_to (int): The ending index (exclusive) of the column range to be included in the new DataFrame.

    Returns:
    pandas.DataFrame: A new DataFrame containing the first column of the original DataFrame as 'CV Section' 
    and the specified range of columns, reindexed starting from 1.
    """
    df_cv_gr0 = df_cv.iloc[:,0].to_frame()
    df_cv_gr0.rename(columns={ df_cv_gr0.columns[0] :'CV Section'},inplace=True)
    df_cv_gr = pd.concat([df_cv_gr0, df_cv.iloc[:, col_from:col_to]], axis=1)
    df_cv_gr.index = list(range(1,5,1))
    return df_cv_gr

df_cv_gr1 = df_grouping(df_cv,1, 5)
df_cv_gr2 = df_grouping(df_cv,5, 9)
df_cv_gr3 = df_grouping(df_cv,10, 14)
df_cv_gr4 = df_grouping(df_cv,14, 18)

def df_transpose_and_format(df_cv_gr): 
    df_cv_gr_T = df_cv_gr.transpose()
    df_cv_gr_T.reset_index(inplace=True)
    df_cv_gr_T.columns = [f'{name}' for name in df_cv_gr_T.iloc[0]]
    df_cv_gr_T.rename( columns= {df_cv_gr_T.columns[0] : 'model'}, inplace= True)
    print(df_cv_gr_T.columns[0])
    df_cv_gr_T.drop(df_cv_gr_T.index[0], inplace= True)
    return df_cv_gr_T

def df_long_format(df_cv_gr_T):
    data = df_cv_gr_T
    df_cv_gr_T_long = pd.melt(data, id_vars=['model'], var_name='CV', value_name='Score')
    return df_cv_gr_T_long

def cv_catplot(data_long,y_min_limit , y_max_limit = 0):
    # Catplot ksztse
    sns.catplot(data=data_long,  y='Score', x='CV', hue='model', kind='bar', height=5, aspect=2)
    # Grafikon cmnek s tengelycmkk belltsa
    plt.title('Model Scores by CV Section')
    plt.xlabel('CV Section')
    plt.ylabel('Score')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)  # Az x tengely cmkinek elforgatsa a jobb olvashatsgrt
    plt.ylim(y_min_limit, y_max_limit)  # Itt lltjuk be a y-tengely hatrait
    plt.gca().invert_yaxis()
    plt.grid()
    # Grafikon megjelentse
    plt.show()

import numpy as np

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from matplotlib.patches import Rectangle
def scatter_plot_models(df,x_min = None, x_max = None, y_min = None, y_max = None):
    # Scatterplot ksztse
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.scatterplot(data=df,  x='std', y='mean', hue='model', style='model', s=100)
    x_min_rect = 0.5
    x_max_rect = 2.0
    y_min_rect = -19
    y_max_rect = -15
    # Tglalap hozzadsa a grafikonhoz, ttetszen
    rect = Rectangle((x_min_rect, y_min_rect), x_max_rect - x_min_rect, y_max_rect - y_min_rect, color='green', alpha=0.3)
    ax.add_patch(rect)
    
    plt.title('Model Performance: Mean vs. Standard Deviation')
    plt.ylabel('Mean CV Score')
    plt.xlabel('Standard Deviation')
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.gca().invert_yaxis()
    plt.xlim((x_min,x_max))
    plt.ylim((y_min,y_max))
    
    # Legend frisstse tbb oszlopra
    plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left', ncol=3)  
    plt.show()
